Preheat oven to 325°F (160°C) In a large bowl, combine oats, quinoa, peanuts, salt and cinnamon. In a small saucepan, combine sugar and honey. Bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly. Turn off heat and stir in peanut butter, oil and vanilla until blended. Pour peanut butter mixture over oat mixture and stir until coated. Spread mixture in a single layer on prepared baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes, stirring twice, until golden brown. Let cool completely on pan. Transfer granola to an airtight container and stir in cranberries. Store at room temperature for up to 2 weeks.